stimulus:
Thank you for signing up to participate in SONA Study 465!
During this study, please focus on the experiment and refrain from activities such as:

- Switching to other tabs on your browser (this will be monitored via the experiment)
- Using your mobile phone/cell phone
- Communicating with others

This way, you are helping to provide data that is useful for psychological research. We thank you for your cooperation!

Welcome to the experiment!

You will now read some instructions about the task. Press the 'Next' button to continue.

On each trial throughout the experiment you will choose between two options,
a Black Square and Black Triangle , as seen below.












Each option results in winning points or receiving 0 points.
There is a 50% chance of either winning or receiving 0 points.

You won't receive the outcome until after a 20 second delay.

As seen above, whether you choose the square or triangle, you will receive a coloured circle after the choice.

This circle will be on screen for 20 seconds until you win points or receive 0 points.

The coloured circle depends on which option you chose.
In the above example, choosing a triangle leads to a green circle and choosing the square leads to a red circle.

Please note: the circles in your task will be different to the above colours.
To reiterate, 50% of the outcomes of each option will be WIN TRIALS, and the other 50% will be NO-WIN TRIALS.

There will be four blocks in the experiment.
You will be given a short 15 second break between each block.

The points and the options will remain the same between the blocks.

The blocks are there just to give you a small break.



The points you earn in the task are also equal to actual money.
1000 points is equal to $1 AUD

This is the rate you will be paid at the experiment's end.
